    "name": "Parametric sensitivity analysis — material properties and contact stiffness",
    "description": "Titanium alloy elastic modulus was varied ±10% and cortical bone surrogate stiffness was varied ±15% across a full-factorial design of 25 FEA runs. Construct stiffness QoI showed <4% variation to modulus perturbation and <7% variation to contact stiffness perturbation, confirming that model predictions are dominated by screw geometry rather than material uncertainty. Yield force predictions were similarly insensitive (CV < 3%), supporting confidence in the nominal model inputs used for validation comparison."
  },
